dcterms:creator: O. Cheikhrouhou
I. Khoufi
dcterms:description: The Multi-objective Traveling Salesman Problem (MOTSP) is a complex optimization problem that requires finding an optimal route visiting multiple cities while minimizing multiple objectives simultaneously.
dcterms:title: Multi-objective Traveling Salesman Problem (MOTSP)

dcterms:creator: G. Reinelt
dcterms:description: RIns (Root Instances) from TSPLIB are standard instances used for testing algorithms for the Traveling Salesman Problem, providing a benchmark for evaluating optimization methods.
dcterms:title: RIns (Root Instances) from TSPLIB

dcterms:creator: K. Li
T. Zhang
R. Wang
dcterms:description: LIns (Leaf Instances) are derived from Root Instances and represent variations of the original problem with different preferences, used to evaluate the performance of optimization algorithms in multi-objective scenarios.
dcterms:title: LIns (Leaf Instances)
